# Line-ending policy.
#
# This repo is developed on Windows with `core.autocrlf=true`, and veeey.net is
# deployed by `git archive` → tarball. Without the rule below, archive exports
# shell scripts with CRLF, so the kernel reads the shebang as
# `#!/usr/bin/env bash\r` and every cron dies with:
#
#     /usr/bin/env: 'bash\r': No such file or directory
#
# That silently took all seven net-sync crons down on 2026-07-20 (including the
# 2-minute stock writeback) — the app itself was fine, so nothing else flagged
# it. Anything executed by an interpreter on the server MUST be LF.
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.bash text eol=lf

# Same reasoning for files a Linux tool parses strictly.
Dockerfile   text eol=lf
*.service    text eol=lf
